elements.name: Quantity
elements.documentation:
Quantity is an M1 class and it has the SysML 1.1 <<ValueType>> stereotype applied to it because this facilitates using this QUDV with SysML 1.1 tools such as MD 16.5.
This QUDV proposal would imply deleting the <<ValueType>> stereotype.

In this QUDV proposal, dimensions are derived according to an extensible dimensional analysis algorithm based on the SystemOfQuantities::baseQuantityKind subset of the SystemOfQuantities::quantityKind collection chosen as the base dimensions for that SystemOfQuantities.

This means that instead of applying the <<ValueType>> stereotype and specifying a Unit and a Dimension for a given <<ValueType>>-stereotyped property type, an end-user can instead specialize the QUDV concept of Quantity, e.g., by redefining Quantity::quantityKind : QuantityKind with one that has a default value for a particular instance specification of a QuantityKind. The same specialization technique can be applied to Quantity::unit and to Quantity::value as well.

The main benefit of this approach compared to <<ValueType>> stereotype approach is that QUDV is an M1 model library and as such is inherently extensible as an M1 model to support rich taxonomies of M1 Quantity concepts organized according to domain-specific criteria specializing and restricting allowed quantity kinds, units and even values.
